pter 160\">Chapter 160</a> <small>(Full Appearance)</small></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"anime_debut\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Anime Debut</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Episode_18\" title=\"Episode 18\">Episode 18</a> <small>(Partial Appearance)</small></div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<section class=\"pi-item pi-group pi-border-color\">\n\t<h2 class=\"pi-item pi-header pi-secondary-font pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background\">Portrayal</h2>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"japanese_va\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">Japanese VA</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mamiko_Noto\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Mamiko Noto\">Mamiko Noto</a></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"pi-item pi-data pi-item-spacing pi-border-color\" data-source=\"english_va\">\n\t\n\t\t<h3 class=\"pi-data-label pi-secondary-font\">English VA</h3>\n\t\n\t<div class=\"pi-data-value pi-font\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jennie_Kwan\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Jennie Kwan\">Jennie Kwan</a></div>\n</div>\n\n</section>\n<nav class=\"pi-navigation pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background pi-secondary-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Kotoha_Hashibira_Images\" title=\"Category:Kotoha Hashibira Images\">Kotoha Hashibira Images</a></nav>\n<nav class=\"pi-navigation pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background pi-secondary-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Kotoha_Hashibira/Image_Gallery\" title=\"Kotoha Hashibira/Image Gallery\">Image Gallery</a></nav>\n</aside>\n<b>Kotoha Hashibira</b><span style=\"font-weight: normal\"> (<span class=\"t_nihongo_kanji\" lang=\"ja\"><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">嘴</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>はし</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">平</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>びら</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby> <ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">琴</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>こと</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">葉</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>は</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby></span><span class=\"t_nihongo_comma\" style=\"display:none\">,</span> <i><span class=\"t_nihongo_romaji\">Hashibira Kotoha</span></i><span class=\"t_nihongo_help\"><sup><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Installing_Japanese_character_sets\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Help:Installing Japanese character sets\"><span class=\"t_nihongo_icon\" style=\"color:#198975;font:bold 80% sans-serif;text-decoration:none;padding:0 .1em;\">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> was the mother of <a href=\"/wiki/Inosuke_Hashibira\" title=\"Inosuke Hashibira\">Inosuke Hashibira</a>.\n<p></p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Personality\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Personality</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Relationships\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Relationships</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Inosuke_Hashibira\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Inosuke Hashibira</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Doma\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Doma</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Abilities_and_Powers\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Abilities and Powers</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Navigation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Navigation</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span></h2>\n<p>Kotoha was described to be a beautiful, young woman, similar in appearance to her son, though Doma stated that she had a softer appearance compared to Inosuke.<sup id=\"cite_ref-auto-5f3a0f1ced13f5842ea7211812bcd9fd_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-auto-5f3a0f1ced13f5842ea7211812bcd9fd-1\">[1]</a></sup> She wore her long, black hair tied up at the end as a bun and had emerald green eyes.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Personality\">Personality</span></h2>\n<p>Kotoha was kind and loving woman. She treasured Inosuke dearly and would always sing lullabies to him when he was a baby, promising to always protect&nbsp;him no matter what.\n</p><p>According to <a href=\"/wiki/Doma\" title=\"Doma\">Doma</a>, she was naive and not very smart.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Relationships\">Relationships</span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Inosuke_Hashibira\"><a href=\"/wiki/Inosuke_Hashibira\" title=\"Inosuke Hashibira\">Inosuke Hashibira</a></span></h3>\n<p>She loved her son immensely and raised him by herself, often singing songs and promising to protect him. In her final moments, she was apologetic to Inosuke for failing him as his mother and guardian.<sup id=\"cite_ref-auto-37e29a12747a079f0adb096813e444f2_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-auto-37e29a12747a079f0adb096813e444f2-2\">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Doma\"><a href=\"/wiki/Doma\" title=\"Doma\">Doma</a></span></h3>\n<p>At the beginning, Kotoha thought that Doma was nice and trustworthy, since he gave her and her baby a shelter when she was in need. However, this changed when she discovered his true identity as a Demon, and how manipulative he was by eating his worshipers. Though, she was killed and later eaten by him while she tried to escape with Inosuke, Doma stated that he never intended to eat her in the first place and was planning to have her by his side until her death, since he enjoyed her company.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<p>Kotoha gave birth to Inosuke at the age of 17 or 18 and was in an abusive relationship with Inosuke's father, as well as with her mother-in-law who bullied her on a daily basis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-auto-6ebcab17925b25488c976ca88c228b76_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-auto-6ebcab17925b25488c976ca88c228b76-3\">[3]</a></sup> One day, during one of his outbursts, she bit her husband's hand, grabbed Inosuke then ran away from the abusive household, fleeing barefoot through the snow. Since she didn't have parents or any siblings to go to, she was running ahead until she reached the Paradise Faith cult, taking shelter as one of the worshipers of <a href=\"/wiki/Doma\" title=\"Doma\">Doma</a> - a leader of the cult. Her husband and his mother chased her there but were soon killed by Doma, who found them to be too noisy, abandoning their corpses in the mountains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-v19_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-v19-4\">[4]</a></sup>\n</p><p>She lived there happily with her son until she suspected that the worshipers were being eaten by Doma. After accusing him of lying to his followers, she ran from the temple with Inosuke in her arms and tried to go through the forest, but was trapped by a cliff. In her final moments, she apologized to Inosuke for failing to protect him and tosses him into the river as an attempt to save his life. She was ultimately killed and eaten by Doma.<sup id=\"cite_ref-auto-ee58402ab61c5f0fa17cf54fe63ee047_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-auto-ee58402ab61c5f0fa17cf54fe63ee047-5\">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Abilities_and_Powers\">Abilities and Powers</span></h2>\n<p>Kotoha was an ordinary human, without any special powers or abilities. Doma stated that she possessed a great talent in singing.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span></h2>\n<ul><li>(To <a href=\"/wiki/Inosuke_Hashibira\" title=\"Inosuke Hashibira\">Inosuke</a>) <i>\"Pinky promise, pinky promise. I will protect you, I promise. Until you get big, your mother will protect you all alone. Sorry Inosuke. You may feel lonely, but I will work hard to protect you in your father's stead. Inosuke, I will protect you even if it costs me my life.\"</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-auto-c4adbf6a05289aa2311f7d9089458b8a_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-auto-c4adbf6a05289aa2311f7d9089458b8a-6\">[6]</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-auto-5f3a0f1ced13f5842ea7211812bcd9fd-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-auto-5f3a0f1ced13f5842ea7211812bcd9fd_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_160\" title=\"Chapter 160\">Chapter 160</a> (Page 6).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-auto-37e29a12747a079f0adb096813e444f2-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-auto-37e29a12747a079f0adb096813e444f2_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_160\" title=\"Chapter 160\">Chapter 160</a> (Page 14).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-auto-6ebcab17925b25488c976ca88c228b76-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-auto-6ebcab17925b25488c976ca88c228b76_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_160\" title=\"Chapter 160\">Chapter 160</a> (Page 5).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-v19-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-v19_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Volume_19\" title=\"Volume 19\">Vol. 19</a>, Extra Pages.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-auto-ee58402ab61c5f0fa17cf54fe63ee047-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-auto-ee58402ab61c5f0fa17cf54fe63ee047_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_160\" title=\"Chapter 160\">Chapter 160</a> (Pages 12-17).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-auto-c4adbf6a05289aa2311f7d9089458b8a-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-auto-c4adbf6a05289aa2311f7d9089458b8a_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kimetsu no Yaiba</i> Manga: <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_160\" title=\"Chapter 160\">Chapter 160</a> (Pages 10-11).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20210113091604\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.144 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.167 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 7208/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 98104/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 39854/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2578/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.009/7.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 798 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  128.914      1 -total